children.subject: I'd strongly doubt it, considering that sophomores (and freshmen) still need to enroll. If you want to enroll in 16B, enroll now.
Recent attitude from faculty teaching the class seems to be if you are junior+ and you don't phase 1 16B you're on your own even if you need it to graduate

history.content: We do not recommend waitlisting EECS 16B in Phase II the chances of getting in will be less likely. If you need this course to graduate you have a better chance of waiting this course in Phase I for FL 21. The professors are really trying to get everyone who Phase 1's the class into the class. Student's shouldn't give up. Sign up for the waitlist because this gives us a sense of the demand for the course and how much to increase the course.
